  "title": "STEEL AND METAL WORKS DRAFTER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Role and Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>· Understand and handle drafting assignments with minimal supervision.</p><p>· Prepare Architectural Metal Work and Steel Structural Shop drawings</p><p>· Review drawings for completeness and accuracy</p><p>· BIM Modelling skills is required</p><p>· Prepare Architectural and Structural Metal Work Shop drawings status reports.</p><p>·Coordinate with main contractors for execution of shop drawings.</p><p>· Maintainproper record for drawings and information</p><p>· Create drawings and models from written and verbal specifications obtained fromEngineer</p><p>· Reviewing and checking sketches and drawings for errors before being sent to productions,vendors, engineers, etc</p><p>· Complete task assigned by superior and performing other relevant duties when needed</p><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><p>.<strong>TRUSTWORTHY & RELIABLE PERSON</strong>.</p><p>· Degree or higher qualifications in Civil Engineering or a Professional certificate</p><p>· Minimum 3 year of drafting experience on Construction Industry, preferably in steelstructure and architectural metal work industry</p><p>· Possess strong initiative, resourceful, independent, meticulous and technologicallyforward-looking</p><p>· Good communication skills and a team player</p><p>· All Pass welcome </p>",
